name: Audi A6 2.0L TFSI QUATTRO "C7.5"
description: Audi A6 C7 series, designated Typ 4G by Audi, began production in 2011 to 2018. It drew a lot of design inspiration from the A8 and has the similar powertrain, the Modular Longitudinal platform, that longitudinal front based engines were constructed under, interior and exterior features. In 2016, sales of the C7 facelift, C7.5 began with this model being among the first to be sold. It features improved exterior styling with design curves that reduced drag effect as with the C7, advanced Matrix LED lights, improved processing capabilities of the Audi MMI infotainment system, an interior wood trimming, and on its drivertrain, holds a 2.0L turbocharged inline 4 cylinder engine with a Dual clutch,  famously S-Tronic, 7 speed automatic transmission. The dual clutch transmission system performs extremely well with sporty driving as it transmits without its torque being interrupted as the clutches are just ready to engage the next gears seamlessly, better than a manual transmission!

name: BMW 535i "F10"
description: The 6th generation of BMW 5 series lasted between the years of 2010 to 2017 where different series including the F10, listed here, F11, F07, and the F18, were also produced. The F10 is a 4 door sedan while the other series' are in different body forms. The 535i under the F10 series was among the first cars in the F10 lineup to be specced with an 8 speed dual clutch automatic transmission gearbox, electric power steering, and an LCD instrument cluster. It packs up over 300 horsepowers in the hood produced by a 3000cc inline 6 twin scroll turbocharged engine. A twin scroll turbocharger basically has two exhaust gas openings in its household caller scrolls. This unit is cool but also can get power angry as you wish!

name: Landrover Discovery IV/ SUNROOF
description: Landrover Discovery has a very rich history of evolution since 1989 when the First Series of the 1st generation was introduced. This is the second generation (L319), Discovery 4, also known as LR4, which was produced from 2009 to 2016. This unit is the last of its generation. Powered by a 3.0L SDV6 engine producing 254 horsepower and 600Nm of torque. It is mated to a ZF 8HP70 automatic transmission gearbox which came as a standard transmission from 2014. It was much upgraded in 2012 to include powerful brakes from Ranger Rover Sport, thicker anti-roll bars for better road handling and a better stability control system that handles issues with understeer as soon as it occurs. It still has fully independent air suspension and electronically locking differentials. This is a pure Marvel!

name: LEXUS IS300h
description: Lexus IS has been in production since 1999 with a lot of redesigns done on the models since then, the Lexus IS 300h in our stock is a Third Gen of the IS series called the XE30 that began in 2013 to 2020. name: Mercedes Benz SLK 200 KOMPRESSOR CONVERTIBLE
description: Mercedes Benz SLK Class, an executive roadster has been in production from the year 1996 until recently in 2020 when Production ended. It was designed to adopt a sporty nature with the weight being tremendously low. This unit is the R171 that was produced between 2004 and 2010.It features an improved aerodynamic efficiency and better strenght from the use of high strength steel. It features a convertible model whose can be easily operated with a record 22 seconds that previously was 3 seconds more. Its heating system was also improved with neck-level heating system being introduced to fully air condition the car especially when it is in convertible mode.

name: Mercedes Benz G63 AMG
description:
Registration: 2022

This spec has an interesting Nardo grey color that appeals very well to a classy eye. It is powered by a 4000cc twin turbocharged handcrafted Petrol V8 engine with an output of 577HP and 850Nm of torque. It is mated to a 9 speed AMG-Speedshift automatic transmission doing 0-100 in 4.5s. It has a premium surround sound system, Burmester, and together with the 12.3 inch digital cluster display, you receive an amazing entertainment experience.

name: Peugeot 3008 GT-Line
description: Peugeot, manufactured in France, first produced the 3008 in 2008 and launched Mid 2009 succeeding Peugeot 4007 and 4008. It is a compact crossover SUV that shares its platform with the 308 which is its smaller counterpart. This unit is the 2nd Generation Peugeot 3008, P84, that succeeded the T84 that ended production in 2015. P84 did a lot of improvements beginning with Peugeot's iCockpit featuring a virtual instrument cluster. The 8 inch display screen with a touch functionality is the center hub of all the car controls. Car controls were designed angularly towards the driver which eases the driver's focus when selecting any control feature. It is also offers a thrilling driving experience. This is a high performance variant with a number of features including lane assist, Blindspot assist, and an exhilarating quick drive.

name: Toyota Landcruiser "VX" VDJ200R
description:
Registration: 2017

As the world moves to the LC300 Series of Landcruiser, you still have a chance to own one of the best rugged good looking offroader, the Landcruiser VX VDJ200R from Australia. It runs on a 4500cc Turbocharged 1VD Diesel V8 engine doing over 650Nm of Torque which is quite powerful and up to task for our roads.
